Here’s an example of using HMPL-DOM to fetch and display data from an API:
html
<div class="container">
  {{#request src="/api/my-component.html"}}
    {{#indicator trigger="pending"}}
      <p>Loading...</p>
    {{/indicator}}
  {{/request}}
</div>

This snippet fetches content from `/api/my-component.html` and displays a loading indicator while waiting for the response.

You can pass `RequestInit` options by defining a `templateFunction` in the configuration. For example:
javascript
import { init } from "hmpl-dom";
init([
  {
    id: "clicker-config",
    value: {
      compile: { memo: true },
      templateFunction: ({ request: { event } }) => ({
        body: JSON.stringify({
          action: event.target.getAttribute("data-action")
        })
      })
    }
  }
]);

This allows customization of API requests, such as setting headers or method types.
